            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>Henry Richard Mozley, of Dudleyville, Tallapoosa County, Ala., was a private in Co. K, 47th Ala.  He served in Virginia and Maryland from 1862 until his death in Apr. 1863.</p>
                                 <p>The collection contains photocopies of Mozley&#039;s letters to his wife Jane and their five children.  The correspondence mainly focuses on family affairs, but Mozley also describes a battlefield after the Seven Days&#039; Battle and shares a &quot;Yankee&quot; prisoner&#039;s views on the length of the war.  Mozley&#039;s death from pleurisy at Springhill Hospital in Farmville, Va., is described in two letters to his widow from John T. Sharpe, a hospital ward master.</p>
                                 <p>Vivian H. Flexman, Mozley&#039;s great-granddaughter, loaned these letters to the Library for photocopying in 1976. She also supplied extracts and summaries of the letters, many copies of which are almost illegible.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


